Ecclesiastes 1:12-18 : Wisdom is Meaningless<br>
Ecclesiastes 2:1-16 : Pleasures are Meaningless<br>
Ecclesiastes 2:17-26 : Toil is Meaningless<br>
Ecclesiastes 4:13-16 : Advancement is Meaningless<br>
Ecclesiastes 5:8-6:12 : Riches are Meaningless<br>
<br>
Sorrow is better than laughter, because a sad face is good for the heart. - Ecclesiastes 7:3<br>
<br>
Is there a more depressing book in the Bible?<br>
<br>
Honestly, what's the point of this book?  Is it perhaps telling us what Jesus prayed about for us?  Jesus prayed we'd be united, is this book just an elaborate way of telling us that there is no reason we should be divided?<br>
<br>
I was thinking of this song earlier, don't know all the words, so I was just repeating these words over and over and over and over and over and over in my head.  (Got quite annoying after awhile.) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
&quot;Sometimes we don't see eye to eye.  We don't agree, we don't know why.  But Jesus prayed that we'd be one.  So for the sake of God's own Son, can we put away our differences, (words I don't know).  It's time we start turning the tide.<br>
<br>
&quot;We have all made enemies of, the ones we're called by Christ to love.&quot;<br>
<br>
It's interesting, I was flipping channels the other day and paused on the INSP network.  Honestly, is there a better way to promote Christianity as boredom (among other negative things) than by use of the tv station?  Sheesh.  Honestly, I was watching some tv preacher speak rather strongly.  He sounded so angry.  Maybe he just only reads this book, Ecclesiastes in the Bible, you suppose? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Does scolding people on the topic of sin really bring about conviction.  Shoot, I'm a Christian and I was flipping the channel rather quickly, clearly I wasn't being convicted. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I'm more convicted through love, not anger.<br>
<br>
Rich Mullins brother, David Mullins once said, &quot;Anger will not reach them for the grace of God.&quot;  I don't like preacher-speak, that's what I call it.  It's the traditional way pastors preach.  I don't know why, it always sounds so fake to me, more showy.  And the more they do it, the more I don't find any depth in what their saying.  Another guy I've seen on INSP and absolutely can not stand because he comes across as such a phony is that Breakthrough guy.  Anyone know who I'm talking about.  He's constantly shouting - &quot;YOU NEED A BREAKTHROUGH!&quot;  Honestly, I sat through about 15 minutes of him once shouting that and he never explained once what I needed a breakthrough about, so I flipped the channel.  All he did for 15 minutes was say in many different elaborations, &quot;YOU NEED A BREAKTHROUGH!&quot;  Yeah, I'd like to break through my screen and punch him on the nose! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And I just love how they add in that little chord of music to add drama to it all.<br>
<br>
Dude, they're just trying to sell you their version of Christianity which puts your money in their pocket.<br>
<br>
Hmm...my thoughts seem to be running random.  This is like a hodgepodge of things and if you ask me what my point is, my point is - if everything is meaningless, seems rather silly for us to isolate others or speak angrily to each other.  Yeah, something like that. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">**********************************************<br>
